recyclables.title: Plastic Water Bottle
recyclables.instruction: Remove all liquid. Plastic caps should be left on. Do NOT place loose caps in the recycling container.

recyclables.title: Cereal Box
recyclables.instruction: All contents removed. Cardboard should be flattened.

recyclables.title: Soup Can
recyclables.instruction: All contents removed. Rinse thoroughly. Remove label and throw in trash.

facts.fact: Americans use an average of 2.5 million plastic bottles every hour, most of which are thrown away.
Toilet paper requires 27,000 trees to be cut down per day.
Humans throw away enough paper and wood each year to heat 50 million houses for 20 years.
Less than 1% of the water supplies found on Earth are usable by people. 97% of water is found in the oceans and 2% exists as frozen water in glaciers, icebergs, permafrost, etc.
Of the 1,200 or more known species of bats that exist, not a single species is blind.
Automatic dishwashers use about 6 gallons of hot water per cycle (over 2,000 gallons per year), which is actually less than the water required to do dishes by hand
The combined weight of the 100 trillion ants on Earth is greater than the combined weight of all 7 billion humans.
Each day, American businesses generate enough paper to circle the Earth 20 times!
